  "justFinishedAt": "2026-03-11T16:29:16.061Z",
  "summary": "## Summary: Add Kanban Tab to Workspace Pages + Tag-Based Board Filtering\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n1. **New \"Kanban\" tab on workspace page detail views** — Users can now click the \"Kanban\" tab on any page to see a scoped Kanban board showing only cards that are tagged with that page's title. This makes it easy to scan through pages and see associated tasks without leaving the workspace.\n\n2. **PageKanbanTab component** — A new component that:\n   - Fetches the user's first/default Kanban board\n   - Filters cards client-side to only show those with a tag matching the page's title (case-insensitive)\n   - Shows a card count badge and inline priority/due date filters\n   - Displays an empty state with instructions on how to associate cards (by adding a matching tag)\n   - Embeds the full KanbanBoard component with drag-and-drop support\n   - Shows loading skeletons and handles edge cases (no board, no matching cards)\n\n3. **Tag filter on the main Kanban board** — Added a new \"All Tags\" dropdown filter to the BoardHeader. When cards have tags, users can filter the entire board to show only cards with a specific tag. This allows filtering by page/smart role from the main board view.\n\n4. **Updated filter logic** — The `applyFilters` function in KanbanBoard now supports tag-based filtering via the new `tag` field in `BoardFilters`.\n\n### Design Decisions\n- **Tag-based association** (not a DB schema change): Cards are associated with pages through their existing tag system. A card tagged \"Architecture\" will appear on the \"Architecture\" page's Kanban tab. This avoids DB migrations, works with existing infrastructure, and is flexible.\n- No database schema changes or migrations needed.\n- TypeScript compiles cleanly with no errors.\n\n### Files Modified\n- `components/pages/PageTabs.tsx` — Added \"kanban\" to `PageTab` type union and tab config\n- `components/pages/tabs/PageKanbanTab.tsx` — **New file** — Scoped Kanban board component for pages\n- `app/(app)/workspace/[workspaceId]/[pageId]/page.tsx` — Import and render PageKanbanTab for the \"kanban\" tab\n- `components/board/BoardHeader.tsx` — Added `tag` field to `BoardFilters`, `availableTags` prop, and tag filter dropdown UI\n- `components/board/KanbanBoard.tsx` — Added tag filtering logic in `applyFilters`\n- `app/(app)/boards/[boardId]/page.tsx` — Added `tag: \"all\"` to default filters, compute `availableTags` from board data, pass to BoardHeader\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- To associate a card with a page, add a tag to the card whose label matches the page's title (case-insensitive matching)\n- The tag filter dropdown on the main board only appears when cards have tags\n- The page Kanban tab uses the user's first board (sorted by most recently updated) — if the user has multiple boards, only the first is shown on the page tab\n- All drag-and-drop, card detail drawer, multi-select, and keyboard shortcuts work within the page Kanban tab since it reuses the full KanbanBoard component"
}